WEBVTT

00:01.214 --> 00:03.290
- Jackpot.
- _

00:03.325 --> 00:04.737
♪♪

00:04.739 --> 00:06.671
One points.

00:06.673 --> 00:10.609
♪♪

00:10.611 --> 00:13.011
Iz raining!

00:13.013 --> 00:14.613
♪♪

00:14.615 --> 00:16.749
Dinner. It's what's for dinner.

00:16.751 --> 00:19.684
Now, I've been up since 10:00,
so I'm turning in.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.886
Enjoy, my babies.

00:21.888 --> 00:24.423
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Channel 36 is incredibly proud</i>

00:24.425 --> 00:26.558
<i>to present our midnight movie,</i>

00:26.560 --> 00:29.762
<i>"The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smowg."</i>

00:29.764 --> 00:34.232
[GASPS] Stan, it's Smowg.
He's about to be desolated.

00:34.234 --> 00:36.135
Stan?

00:37.404 --> 00:39.404
Huh.

00:39.506 --> 00:41.340
Huh.

00:41.442 --> 00:43.141
Huh.

00:43.243 --> 00:45.043
Huh.

00:45.045 --> 00:47.312
No.

00:51.485 --> 00:52.517
Uh-oh.

00:52.519 --> 00:54.452
What the hell are you
guys doing down here?

00:54.454 --> 00:57.656
Uh, you know how you never
learned what lacrosse is?

00:57.658 --> 00:58.857
Yeah?

00:58.859 --> 00:59.858
Well, this is it.

00:59.860 --> 01:01.860
This is lacrosse.

01:01.862 --> 01:04.529
♪♪

01:04.531 --> 01:07.466
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:07.468 --> 01:10.869
♪ I got a feelin'
that it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:10.871 --> 01:13.872
♪ The sun in the sky has
a smile on his face ♪

01:13.874 --> 01:18.544
♪ And he's shinin'
a salute to the American race ♪

01:20.214 --> 01:23.748
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

01:23.750 --> 01:26.485
- ♪ Good... ♪
- ♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:26.487 --> 01:27.586
Aah!

01:28.489 --> 01:31.623
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

01:32.349 --> 01:34.426
So, every night after I'm asleep,

01:34.428 --> 01:36.428
you come down to the crawl space?

01:36.930 --> 01:38.863
I don't understand.

01:38.865 --> 01:41.265
A crawl space is an area between floors,

01:41.267 --> 01:43.401
where crawling is not just allowed,

01:43.403 --> 01:44.536
it's encouraged...

01:44.538 --> 01:46.338
I know what a crawl space is, Stan.

01:46.340 --> 01:47.739
Did you, though?

01:47.741 --> 01:50.274
I mean, why are you eating down here?

01:50.276 --> 01:53.144
Are you hiding from me?

01:53.146 --> 01:54.879
Just give it to me straight.

01:54.881 --> 01:56.748
We're still hungry
'cause your dinner stinks!

01:56.750 --> 01:57.682
- It sucks!
- Whoa!

01:57.684 --> 01:58.750
- Easy!
- Hey!

01:58.752 --> 02:01.686
- [CHUCKLES]
- Uh, we hate you.

02:01.688 --> 02:03.688
- You're a bad lady!
- Jeff!

02:03.690 --> 02:04.889
Alright, that's it.

02:04.891 --> 02:06.157
Go to the dark part of the crawl space

02:06.159 --> 02:08.693
- for 10 minutes.
- It's ridiculous.

02:08.695 --> 02:10.895
The dinner was bad?

02:10.896 --> 02:13.097
I followed the recipe to a "T."

02:13.099 --> 02:17.101
It was Certified "Yim Yam Yummo"
by Rachael Ray herself!

02:17.103 --> 02:19.571
It's not that your cooking's bad...

02:19.573 --> 02:22.840
Gee, how do we put it gently, gang?

02:22.842 --> 02:25.043
- Your food is soulless.
- Totally uninspired.

02:25.045 --> 02:27.178
- It's got no heart!
- Oh.

02:27.180 --> 02:28.512
Sorry, Mom.

02:28.514 --> 02:29.781
JEFF: It's poop food!

02:29.783 --> 02:31.383
Jeff! 20 minutes!

02:31.385 --> 02:33.051
Life is so unfair!

02:33.053 --> 02:35.787
Don't feel bad, Mom.
Cooking's just not your thing.

02:35.789 --> 02:36.988
You can always join us here,

02:36.990 --> 02:38.456
for what we call "Cracker Hour."

02:38.458 --> 02:40.858
Oh, but it's so much more than crackers.

02:40.860 --> 02:43.327
There's cheeses, toasted Pringles,

02:43.329 --> 02:45.329
and sumptuous summer sausages.

02:45.331 --> 02:49.133
Hillshire Farms has put more
love into this Li'l Smoky

02:49.135 --> 02:52.003
than in a thousand of your "dinners."

02:52.005 --> 02:54.005
I don't want to be bad at cooking.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.607
I want to be good at cooking.

02:55.609 --> 02:58.076
Why not do a cooking course
at the Learning Annex?

02:58.078 --> 02:59.744
You tell them what you want to learn,

02:59.746 --> 03:02.747
they look it up on the Internet,
and then they teach it to you.

03:02.749 --> 03:05.349
You know what? I <i> will</i> do that.

03:05.351 --> 03:08.152
Sorry I drove you guys underground.

03:08.154 --> 03:11.022
I scratched myself on a nail!

03:11.024 --> 03:13.758
[CHUCKLES] Gotta watch
out for those nails.

03:13.760 --> 03:16.027
Hold up... Do my eyes spy

03:16.029 --> 03:19.564
a Li'l Smoky in the dirt?

03:19.566 --> 03:22.100
- Dad, are you okay?
- There's a nail in his head!

03:22.102 --> 03:24.035
- Why isn't he speaking?
- Somebody do something!

03:24.037 --> 03:26.370
- This is literally the first time tonight...
- Aw, Dad! He's so still!

03:26.372 --> 03:28.306
- ...I've reached for the Li'l Smokys and not bumped...
- Blink if you can hear me!

03:28.308 --> 03:29.741
- ...into Stan's hand.
- He's not blinking! He's so calm!

03:30.757 --> 03:32.844
- ♪♪
- _

03:32.846 --> 03:34.111
Don't worry.

03:34.113 --> 03:35.713
Stan's walking around and everything,

03:35.715 --> 03:37.248
but he hasn't said a word,

03:37.250 --> 03:39.985
so you know that nail's
touching something important.

03:39.987 --> 03:42.119
You want to talk about
touching a nerve...

03:42.121 --> 03:45.723
You guys not liking my
cooking has really rattled me.

03:45.725 --> 03:49.460
Yes, yes it is me. Miss Nadine.

03:49.462 --> 03:51.262
Yeah, Nadine!

03:51.264 --> 03:54.599
Today, we're making a classic
spaghetti and meatballs.

03:54.601 --> 03:56.868
Every step is on these recipe cards,

03:56.870 --> 03:58.269
except for one...

03:58.271 --> 03:59.470
Enjoy yourself!

03:59.472 --> 04:01.939
I'll just follow the steps on the card,

04:01.941 --> 04:03.675
if that's okay with you.

04:03.677 --> 04:06.477
Oh, man, that babe Danuta's here!

04:06.479 --> 04:09.214
I'm gonna make a cool face
while I chop my onion.

04:10.950 --> 04:14.285
Is she looking? Is this face cool?

04:14.287 --> 04:17.288
Hmm. My cup has a dent in it.

04:17.290 --> 04:19.290
Won't be accurate.

04:19.291 --> 04:21.625
I'll have to use 48 teaspoons.

04:21.628 --> 04:23.294
[GASPS]

04:23.296 --> 04:26.698
Ms. Nadine!
Dick's not measuring his salt.

04:26.700 --> 04:28.833
Oh. Well, that's fine.

04:28.835 --> 04:30.968
He just squeezed a lemon in there.

04:30.970 --> 04:32.370
That's not in the recipe.

04:32.372 --> 04:34.239
Your back was turned and he squeezed it!

04:34.241 --> 04:36.241
- I saw!
- I thought a hit of lemon

04:36.243 --> 04:38.443
would brighten up the marinara.

04:39.667 --> 04:40.845
Mmm.

04:40.847 --> 04:42.313
Ooh. That's a nice change, Dick.

04:42.315 --> 04:45.851
There's no lemon
anywhere in this recipe.

04:45.853 --> 04:48.586
Has the whole world gone crazy?

04:48.588 --> 04:50.722
[SOBBING] Danuta...

04:50.724 --> 04:54.659
Look at me, Danuta.

04:54.661 --> 04:57.528
- ♪♪
- _

04:57.530 --> 05:00.531
The nail has only pierced
his speech centers.

05:00.533 --> 05:03.334
I can yank it out with my Leatherman,
no problem,

05:03.336 --> 05:06.003
but not until the brain
swelling goes down.

05:06.005 --> 05:08.673
Bigger question... Would you be willing

05:08.675 --> 05:10.608
to let me have the brain?

05:10.610 --> 05:13.344
Keep in mind,
I'd replace it with a bag of sand

05:13.346 --> 05:16.281
so his overall weight
would not change...

05:16.283 --> 05:19.617
No. How long will it take
the swelling to go down?

05:20.318 --> 05:22.019
One week.

05:22.021 --> 05:25.290
I'll put this tiny safety
cone on it for now,

05:25.292 --> 05:29.094
but as your physician,
I must advise that you,

05:29.096 --> 05:34.231
as soon as possible,
get him a fun new hat.

05:34.233 --> 05:36.701
It's a Bugle snack.

05:36.703 --> 05:38.369
Mm. It's delicious.

05:38.371 --> 05:41.439
Hooraaaaay!

05:43.242 --> 05:46.444
Mmm. I know I keep saying this,

05:46.446 --> 05:48.980
but, to quote Dom DeLuise's tombstone,

05:48.982 --> 05:52.717
great meatball.

05:53.482 --> 05:55.787
And... what is this?

05:55.789 --> 05:57.388
It's also a meatball.

05:57.390 --> 05:58.656
Oh.

05:58.658 --> 05:59.724
It's good.

05:59.726 --> 06:01.793
Hey! Tell me the truth.

06:01.795 --> 06:04.395
- I can take it.
- Okay.

06:04.397 --> 06:05.863
It's a little bland.

06:05.865 --> 06:07.132
[SCREAMS]

06:07.134 --> 06:09.266
- It was <i> your</i> recipe!
- [GLASS SHATTERS]

06:09.268 --> 06:11.336
And I followed it to the letter!

06:11.338 --> 06:14.205
- [GLASS SHATTERS]
- I want a 40% refund!

06:14.207 --> 06:16.073
Get her out of here!

06:16.075 --> 06:19.010
[GRUNTING] Let me tell you something.

06:19.012 --> 06:20.878
Oh, yeah? What?

06:20.880 --> 06:24.215
This whole Annex is gonna burn,

06:24.217 --> 06:26.684
and you're gonna be in it.

06:26.686 --> 06:28.419
You can't burn brick, bitch!

06:28.421 --> 06:31.356
Oh, I'll find a fire hot enough.

06:31.358 --> 06:34.025
You're gonna pop like popcorn.

06:34.027 --> 06:36.962
Pop! Pop-pop-pop-pop-pop!

06:36.964 --> 06:40.031
[ <i> JAZZ MUSIC PLAYS</i> ]

06:40.033 --> 06:41.699
<i>Now it's time for a new segment</i>

06:41.701 --> 06:43.368
<i>that I'm really excited about...</i>

06:43.370 --> 06:46.303
- <i>So [BLEEP] excited.
- ...where I travel the globe</i>

06:46.305 --> 06:48.173
<i>interviewing famous chefs.</i>

06:48.175 --> 06:51.042
<i>Here's me with Patagonian super chef,</i>

06:51.044 --> 06:52.910
<i>Francis Mallmann.</i>

06:52.912 --> 06:54.512
<i>Super</i> chef?

06:54.514 --> 06:57.849
As I say in my book, "The Seven Fires,"

06:57.851 --> 06:59.317
the problem with the home cook

06:59.319 --> 07:01.987
is that they are
enslaved by the recipes,

07:01.989 --> 07:04.656
by their electric stoves.

07:04.658 --> 07:06.457
MALLMANN: <i>In the outdoors, where I cook,</i>

07:06.459 --> 07:09.126
<i>man is returned to what is essential.</i>

07:09.128 --> 07:10.795
<i>The fire Promethean.</i>

07:10.797 --> 07:13.298
<i>It's all in my book, "The Seven Fires."</i>

07:15.402 --> 07:19.537
Well, the results are in.
Slap bracelets are back.

07:19.539 --> 07:20.738
What the hell?!

07:20.740 --> 07:22.340
Damn thing made me look like an idiot.

07:22.342 --> 07:24.542
Wow, you're reading Francis Mallmann?

07:24.544 --> 07:28.079
Yeah, but his cooking is all
about trusting your instincts,

07:28.081 --> 07:30.015
and I don't know if I have those.

07:30.017 --> 07:32.083
What if you could learn instincts

07:32.085 --> 07:34.151
from someone like Francis Mallmann?

07:34.153 --> 07:35.753
Oh, my God. Do you know him?

07:35.755 --> 07:38.556
Yes, but we're estranged.
I said someone <i> like</i> him.

07:38.558 --> 07:40.758
I have a persona that borrows heavily

07:40.760 --> 07:42.560
from Francis... duplicates him really,

07:42.562 --> 07:43.961
probably the source of the rift...

07:43.963 --> 07:45.630
and I <i> do</i> know that persona.

07:45.632 --> 07:47.965
Would you be willing to go
all the way to Patagonia

07:47.967 --> 07:49.034
to learn how to cook?

07:49.036 --> 07:52.370
Roger, I'd go to freakin' L.L. Bean

07:52.372 --> 07:54.171
if it helped me be a better cook.

07:54.173 --> 07:55.707
Ha! That's hilarious.

07:55.709 --> 08:00.478
Although maybe you
aren't <i> being</i> hilarious.

08:00.479 --> 08:01.879
_

08:01.915 --> 08:03.848
Now, Francine, when we get there,

08:03.850 --> 08:05.250
this guy's gonna be me.

08:05.252 --> 08:06.451
I want to be clear about that.

08:06.453 --> 08:08.786
This persona and I are different,

08:08.788 --> 08:09.987
but I am him.

08:09.989 --> 08:11.589
I can imagine how jarring it is

08:11.591 --> 08:13.791
to find me around every
corner in your life,

08:13.793 --> 08:15.927
and I want this to be a
smoother deal for you.

08:15.929 --> 08:17.328
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

08:17.330 --> 08:18.796
This is it, right?

08:18.798 --> 08:21.332
I'm about to look over,
and he'll be there,

08:21.334 --> 08:23.334
- and you'll be gone.
- Yeah.

08:23.336 --> 08:25.537
You know,
I don't usually get to say goodbye.

08:25.539 --> 08:28.740
Well, thanks for flying down with me.

08:28.742 --> 08:31.609
Even if you had to come
anyway to be the guy.

08:31.611 --> 08:32.809
Thanks.

08:32.812 --> 08:36.881
I'm Frenchus Mallmank,
<i>not</i> Francis Mallmann,

08:36.884 --> 08:38.149
and I'm gonna challenge

08:38.150 --> 08:40.351
everything you know about cooking.

08:40.352 --> 08:41.619
[GASPS]

08:41.621 --> 08:43.087
Goodbye!

08:43.090 --> 08:44.422
[SIGHS] Alright.

08:44.424 --> 08:47.325
That's enough turning around.

08:49.696 --> 08:51.496
♪♪

08:51.498 --> 08:53.298
NARRATOR: <i> Frenchus Mallmank</i>

08:53.300 --> 08:55.900
<i>rejected the pathway
of fine French cuisine,</i>

08:55.902 --> 09:00.171
<i>and dedicated himself to powerful,
primitive cooking.</i>

09:00.173 --> 09:02.307
<i>On his island in Patagonia,</i>

09:02.309 --> 09:04.309
<i>with his dedicated students,</i>

09:04.311 --> 09:06.444
<i>he makes incredible meals</i>

09:06.446 --> 09:09.514
<i>using little more than fire and salt...</i>

09:09.516 --> 09:13.318
and the world has taken notice.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.786
[EXASPERATEDLY] Would you shut up!

09:15.788 --> 09:18.189
Why are you narrating everything?

09:18.191 --> 09:20.191
And the narrator withdrew,

09:20.193 --> 09:23.127
shutting himself off
from human connection...

09:23.129 --> 09:24.929
Good! I think that's good.

09:24.931 --> 09:25.997
There.

09:25.999 --> 09:28.266
That is how you build...

09:28.268 --> 09:30.601
the Eight Fires.

09:30.603 --> 09:33.672
♪♪

09:33.674 --> 09:36.607
Yes. One more than Francis.

09:36.609 --> 09:38.409
Now I'll teach my techniques,

09:38.411 --> 09:40.545
all leading up to a grand feast.

09:40.547 --> 09:43.548
I will try each of your dishes,
finishing many of them,

09:43.550 --> 09:45.283
and see how much you learned.

09:45.285 --> 09:46.751
Lesson one!

09:46.753 --> 09:48.353
I'm sealing this fish

09:48.355 --> 09:51.089
in the rich cream mud
that is here by my feet.

09:51.091 --> 09:52.691
When I cook this in the fire,

09:52.693 --> 09:54.959
the mud will hold in the moisture.

09:54.961 --> 09:57.828
- It will also muffle the small screams of the fish...
- [HIGH-PITCHED SQUEALING]

09:57.830 --> 09:59.430
...as it suffers and dies.

09:59.432 --> 10:02.233
Oh! How many cups of mud is that?

10:02.235 --> 10:04.903
You have long fingers,
and it looks like a lot.

10:04.905 --> 10:06.505
No cups! No recipes!

10:06.507 --> 10:11.442
Cooking is about being free and alive.

10:11.444 --> 10:13.111
No!

10:13.113 --> 10:15.714
Eh? You like my trebuchet?

10:15.716 --> 10:17.115
- ♪♪
- _

10:17.117 --> 10:18.649
- [PIANO PLAYS]
- Alright.

10:18.651 --> 10:21.252
Let's find Dad a hat
to cover up that nail.

10:21.254 --> 10:22.587
[PIANO CONTINUES]

10:22.589 --> 10:24.389
You like the piano, Dad?

10:24.391 --> 10:27.258
You can wait here
while we shop for hats,

10:27.260 --> 10:29.460
and I won't have to look at the nail.

10:29.462 --> 10:32.197
Hey, look who it is!

10:32.199 --> 10:35.600
[PIANO CONTINUES]

10:35.602 --> 10:37.468
- 10 minute break.
- [PIANO STOPS]

10:37.470 --> 10:41.173
Just enough time for a cigarette
and a tuna-fish sandwich.

10:44.877 --> 10:47.946
[PIANO PLAYS]

10:47.948 --> 10:48.947
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

10:48.949 --> 10:51.282
I am the manager of this Nordstrom,

10:51.284 --> 10:54.285
and that is simply gorgeous playing.

10:54.287 --> 10:55.286
You're hired.

10:55.288 --> 10:56.888
And you're fired.

10:56.890 --> 11:00.358
Does Dick's Sporting
Goods have piano players?

11:00.360 --> 11:01.760
Dad can't play piano.

11:01.762 --> 11:04.563
It's the nail. It's unlocking him.

11:04.565 --> 11:08.499
My nail gives me the power to
know all domestic flight times

11:08.501 --> 11:11.302
within the United States.

11:11.304 --> 11:15.840
<i>United 12</i> leaves Dulles
for O'Hare in 30 minutes.

11:15.842 --> 11:18.909
No. Not even close.

11:18.911 --> 11:20.512
[SIZZLING]

11:23.049 --> 11:25.450
Come, my acolytes. Taste.

11:25.452 --> 11:27.518
You just got a bunch of dirt in it.

11:27.520 --> 11:30.521
That's earth,
and earth is flavor and passion.

11:30.523 --> 11:33.658
Think of how many people
had sex on this earth.

11:33.660 --> 11:35.526
And on earth!

11:35.528 --> 11:37.528
[WHISPERING] I found a
little piece that's clean.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.330
A little dirt for ya!

11:39.332 --> 11:41.332
- [FIRE CRACKLING]
- To cook meat over flame,

11:41.334 --> 11:43.001
to me, I believe truly...

11:43.003 --> 11:45.604
Can't find the neck hole in this poncho.
There it is.

11:45.606 --> 11:48.406
The best technique is spatchcocking.

11:48.408 --> 11:49.674
[WHISPERING] I've done that.

11:49.676 --> 11:51.610
It's when you intentionally graze

11:51.612 --> 11:53.744
someone's penis with your backpack.

11:53.746 --> 11:56.948
Spatchcocking is when you
flatten an animal's ribcage

11:56.950 --> 11:58.549
so that it cooks more evenly.

11:58.551 --> 12:00.685
I'll show you.

12:00.687 --> 12:04.555
It's all about finding just
the right point of pressure,

12:04.557 --> 12:07.091
feeling it, making that connection,

12:07.093 --> 12:09.360
and then spatchcock!

12:09.362 --> 12:11.162
This works with any meat.

12:11.164 --> 12:13.231
Wild hare...

12:13.233 --> 12:15.967
river otter...

12:15.969 --> 12:17.702
two chickens.

12:17.704 --> 12:19.638
Usually, you want to prep it,
get the guts out,

12:19.640 --> 12:21.372
but I was just feeling it too hard.

12:21.374 --> 12:22.641
Had to do a live spatchcock.

12:22.643 --> 12:25.644
So it goes.
Eight fires, etcetera, etcetera.

12:25.646 --> 12:28.112
With food, you need a little wine.

12:28.114 --> 12:30.448
This, to me, is a little wine.

12:30.450 --> 12:33.117
This is the largest size bottle of wine

12:33.119 --> 12:34.585
that isn't legally a vat.

12:34.587 --> 12:36.387
It is called... a nebuchadnezzar.

12:36.389 --> 12:39.524
I drink four of these a day,
just like Charlemagne did,

12:39.526 --> 12:40.925
and I'll outlive you all.

12:40.927 --> 12:43.394
What is it the poets say about wine?

12:43.396 --> 12:45.796
[BELCHES]

12:45.798 --> 12:47.866
What? Did you say something?

12:47.868 --> 12:49.000
Was I still going?

12:49.002 --> 12:50.268
Well, you're a fool

12:50.270 --> 12:54.406
if you don't savor your nebuchadnezzars.

12:56.677 --> 12:59.010
I can't tell if it's done.

12:59.012 --> 13:02.080
Maybe I should check real quick.

13:02.082 --> 13:03.414
It's ruined.

13:03.416 --> 13:06.084
The precious juice has been drained.

13:06.086 --> 13:09.754
Taste yours.

13:09.756 --> 13:12.290
Now try mine.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.491
Mmm.

13:13.493 --> 13:15.360
It's so good.

13:15.362 --> 13:16.827
You're resisting my lessons.

13:16.829 --> 13:19.030
I hope you can show me
something at the big feast.

13:19.032 --> 13:21.499
Now, if you excuse me, I must slumber

13:21.501 --> 13:23.502
and dream of spatchcocking T-rexes

13:23.504 --> 13:26.371
with my childhood friend, Jean-Baptiste.

13:26.373 --> 13:29.507
[PIANO PLAYS]

13:29.509 --> 13:31.642
[GIGGLES] Business
has never been better,

13:31.644 --> 13:33.244
and it's all thanks to you!

13:33.246 --> 13:37.582
Sales figures correspond
100% with your piano playing!

13:37.584 --> 13:39.250
I don't want any of this stuff.

13:39.252 --> 13:40.719
[UP-TEMPO PIANO PLAYS]

13:40.721 --> 13:43.388
I'm buying 10 winter coats!

13:43.390 --> 13:44.589
[LAUGHS]

13:44.591 --> 13:46.124
You hooked another one, Nailhead!

13:46.126 --> 13:48.793
And you know how big the
margins are on coats.

13:48.795 --> 13:50.661
[CHUCKLES] Oh, oh!

13:50.663 --> 13:53.732
By the way,
I got a call from corporate earlier.

13:53.734 --> 13:56.667
They're considering turning
the Langley Falls location

13:56.669 --> 13:59.203
into the new flagship...

13:59.205 --> 14:00.805
[PIANO CONTINUES]

14:00.807 --> 14:01.940
Yes.

14:01.942 --> 14:03.608
Flagship.

14:03.610 --> 14:06.745
That's what all this has been about.

14:06.747 --> 14:08.747
Now, play me to the break room,

14:08.749 --> 14:12.683
this time in the style of
a silent-movie villain.

14:12.685 --> 14:16.655
[STACCATO NOTES PLAY]

14:22.295 --> 14:26.965
Javier, your Potatoes Three
Ways is delicious, inspired.

14:26.967 --> 14:29.167
What would you say to another three-ways

14:29.169 --> 14:31.102
- in my big fur bed?
- No.

14:31.104 --> 14:35.239
You deny me?
My passion grows like a bonfire!

14:35.241 --> 14:36.507
Anywho, moving on.

14:36.509 --> 14:38.443
I was having a tough time at first,

14:38.445 --> 14:42.380
but I think I finally cooked
from... here.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.349
Promising.

14:49.122 --> 14:50.321
Where are they?

14:50.323 --> 14:51.722
Where are what?

14:51.724 --> 14:54.259
The measuring cups that
you used to make this!

14:54.261 --> 14:55.860
You're right!

14:55.862 --> 14:57.528
I cheated.

14:57.530 --> 14:59.464
I've been doing so terribly.

14:59.466 --> 15:01.874
Oh, why can't I understand how to cook?!

15:01.909 --> 15:03.001
Who cares about that?!

15:03.003 --> 15:05.604
I launched those measuring cups
all the way to Bear Island.

15:05.606 --> 15:07.872
If you went there, it's possible "they"

15:07.874 --> 15:09.674
followed your scent back here.

15:09.676 --> 15:11.843
- Who?
- [BEARS GROWL]

15:12.813 --> 15:16.214
Acolytes, fly me to safety!

15:16.216 --> 15:18.683
We'll tell the world your story!

15:18.685 --> 15:21.620
But I already told the world my story.

15:21.622 --> 15:23.622
[BEARS GROWL]

15:23.624 --> 15:25.356
Roger, what do we do?

15:25.358 --> 15:27.892
[WHISPERING] Stand perfectly
still and don't make a sound.

15:27.894 --> 15:30.495
[SNIFFING]

15:30.497 --> 15:32.430
- Yes, it's me.
- [ROARS]

15:32.432 --> 15:35.033
[SCREAMING]

15:35.035 --> 15:37.435
♪♪

15:37.437 --> 15:39.237
- [GROWLS]
- [SCREAMING CONTINUES]

15:39.239 --> 15:43.441
♪♪

15:43.443 --> 15:45.710
[COUGHS]

15:45.712 --> 15:48.446
That damn bear spatchcocked me.

15:48.448 --> 15:50.781
I wish I wasn't here right now.

15:50.783 --> 15:54.419
I wish I was in a restaurant.

15:56.390 --> 15:58.056
♪♪

15:58.058 --> 15:59.924
Roger! Are you okay?

15:59.926 --> 16:02.326
They told me Bear Island
would be a problem

16:02.328 --> 16:03.395
when I bought this place.

16:03.397 --> 16:05.529
"Leave the bears to me," I said.

16:05.531 --> 16:07.799
What did I even mean?
I didn't have a plan.

16:07.801 --> 16:09.200
This is all <i> my</i> fault.

16:09.202 --> 16:10.668
It's not your fault.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.804
You weren't there when
I bought the island.

16:12.806 --> 16:14.272
I mean, if I hadn't cheated,

16:14.274 --> 16:16.540
the bears never would have come here.

16:16.542 --> 16:18.410
You killed me.

16:18.412 --> 16:20.612
Let's see how badly you're hurt.

16:20.614 --> 16:22.013
What's the damage?

16:22.015 --> 16:24.616
Will I ever be able
to rollerblade again?

16:24.618 --> 16:27.419
[SIGHING] Oh. That bear really got you.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.221
We need to get you off this island,

16:29.223 --> 16:30.688
but the boat is gone.

16:30.690 --> 16:33.024
There's a backup boat on the
other side of the island.

16:33.026 --> 16:34.558
Oh, my God!

16:34.560 --> 16:36.494
Wait, why do you have a backup boat?

16:36.496 --> 16:39.831
You should be asking,
why do I have three boats.

16:39.833 --> 16:44.436
Because I used to,
but then I ended up selling one.

16:44.438 --> 16:49.641
- [GRUNTS]
- Ow. Ow. Ow.

16:49.643 --> 16:51.976
Wait! My nebuchadnezzars!

16:51.978 --> 16:55.179
- [GLASS CLINKING]
- Ow. Ow.

16:55.181 --> 16:56.915
Wait, my gaucho hat!

16:58.318 --> 17:02.053
[STRAINED] You know, Francine,
I think I'm ready to die.

17:02.055 --> 17:05.056
There's just one last
thing I want to do...

17:05.058 --> 17:07.058
drink a live-forever potion.

17:07.060 --> 17:10.462
You're not gonna die.
We've reached the boat.

17:10.464 --> 17:12.063
Wait. There's somebody in it.

17:12.065 --> 17:14.799
Oh, no. It's Francis Mallmann.

17:14.800 --> 17:17.669
You stole my identity,
Frenchus Mallmank,

17:17.671 --> 17:21.406
and now I steal your boat!

17:24.144 --> 17:25.542
[PIANO PLAYS]

17:25.545 --> 17:28.212
♪♪

17:28.214 --> 17:30.682
Money! Oh, money! Oh, money!

17:30.684 --> 17:32.550
[CHUCKLES] We're rich!

17:32.552 --> 17:35.086
This branch of Nordstrom is rich!

17:35.088 --> 17:37.689
- Oh, no. The family.
- It's been a week.

17:37.691 --> 17:39.291
We have to take the nail out now.

17:39.293 --> 17:42.494
- Otherwise, he'll die, right, Dr. Kalgary?
- Sounds right.

17:42.496 --> 17:45.429
Then you must take it out.

17:45.431 --> 17:47.431
I'd never want Nailhead to die.

17:47.433 --> 17:48.766
Because, you see,

17:48.768 --> 17:50.969
it wasn't about the money
or the coat sales...

17:50.971 --> 17:53.037
the highest in the tri-county area.

17:53.039 --> 17:55.307
It was about the music.

17:55.309 --> 18:00.244
So before you remove the nail,
could I hear just one last song?

18:00.246 --> 18:03.315
Dad! One more song!

18:03.317 --> 18:06.117
[PIANO PLAYS MELANCHOLY TUNE]

18:06.119 --> 18:08.586
No boats. No food.

18:08.588 --> 18:10.654
We're both gonna starve here.

18:10.656 --> 18:12.190
I'm surprised I made it this far

18:12.192 --> 18:15.660
with the amount of glass
I've been drinking.

18:15.662 --> 18:17.529
Before we die,

18:17.531 --> 18:20.198
why did you cheat with
the measuring cups?

18:20.200 --> 18:22.066
I didn't want to mess up, I guess.

18:22.068 --> 18:25.003
What would it mean if you messed up?

18:25.005 --> 18:26.938
That there was something wrong

18:26.940 --> 18:29.140
with the measurements or the recipe.

18:29.142 --> 18:32.544
And what if you messed
up without a recipe?

18:32.546 --> 18:34.012
What if it was just you,

18:34.014 --> 18:36.414
cooking, making your own decisions?

18:36.416 --> 18:39.817
It'd mean that there was
something wrong with <i> me,</i>

18:39.819 --> 18:41.485
that <i> I</i> was the failure.

18:41.487 --> 18:45.623
And that's what therapists
call a babababingo.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.625
[COUGHS]

18:47.627 --> 18:50.494
Roger, this leg is starting to turn.

18:50.496 --> 18:52.364
I think I should cut it off.

18:52.366 --> 18:56.434
If you're gonna cut off my leg,
you need to cook it.

18:56.436 --> 18:57.969
Roger, that's crazy!

18:57.971 --> 19:00.172
It'll keep me from
dying of blood poisoning

19:00.174 --> 19:02.707
and give us both something to eat.

19:02.709 --> 19:04.108
Oh, I don't know.

19:04.110 --> 19:06.310
There is no recipe for cooking my leg,

19:06.312 --> 19:07.579
no safety net.

19:07.581 --> 19:11.315
Show me who you are and feed me me.

19:11.317 --> 19:14.652
[PIANO CONTINUES]

19:14.654 --> 19:21.859
♪♪

19:21.861 --> 19:23.661
[GROANING]

19:23.663 --> 19:32.470
♪♪

19:32.472 --> 19:41.213
♪♪

19:41.215 --> 19:42.414
I had a lemon.

19:42.416 --> 19:51.022
♪♪

19:51.024 --> 19:59.697
♪♪

19:59.699 --> 20:01.499
It's delicious, Franny.

20:01.501 --> 20:05.903
♪♪

20:05.905 --> 20:08.640
- [BODY THUDS]
- [DISSONANT NOTES PLAY]

20:08.642 --> 20:10.775
Hey, I'm back, baby.

20:10.777 --> 20:13.511
No! Put it back in! Put it back in!

20:13.513 --> 20:15.080
[MANAGER SCREAMS]

20:16.783 --> 20:18.783
- [SCREAMING CONTINUES]
- [CUSTOMERS SHOUT INDISTINCTLY]

20:18.785 --> 20:21.986
Don't worry! I'll make you a monster!

20:21.988 --> 20:24.255
Billy, get the van!

20:25.317 --> 20:28.793
Ah, it feels good
to have conquered this.

20:28.795 --> 20:30.862
I was letting my fear of failing

20:30.864 --> 20:32.864
make me a boring cook.

20:32.866 --> 20:34.532
[BEARS GROWL]

20:34.534 --> 20:35.867
[SCREAMS]

20:35.869 --> 20:37.669
No! Don't fight them.

20:38.444 --> 20:40.272
Feed them.

20:40.274 --> 20:41.806
[BEAR GROWLS]

20:41.808 --> 20:43.808
Hey, it's Francis.

20:43.810 --> 20:45.477
The smell of your soulful cooking

20:45.479 --> 20:47.145
lured him back, Francine.

20:47.147 --> 20:50.414
And I've hit my goal weight.

20:51.343 --> 20:53.751
Roger, your body's
gonna grow back, right?

20:53.753 --> 20:55.753
It always has before.

20:55.755 --> 20:58.490
Oh, God! What if it doesn't?!

20:58.492 --> 21:00.692
Have a good night!

